# 🧠 2. Core Concept: The Server Is God

The backend controls:

* Player states
* Roles
* Votes
* Alive/dead status
* Phase (day/night)
* Win detection

Clients:

* Only send actions
* Never decide results

This prevents cheating and keeps logic clean.

---

# 🧩 3. Core Data Models (Conceptual Only)

You’ll need structured models like:

### Game

* id
* phase (lobby / day / night / ended)
* players
* roles
* anonymous_voting (bool)
* nominations
* votes
* winner

### Player

* id
* username
* role_id
* alive (bool)
* connected (bool)

### Role

* id
* name
* description
* win_condition
* night_action_type (optional)
* team (mafia / village / neutral / custom)

Everything revolves around these 3.

