# 🔥 Now Let’s Break Down Your 10 Core Features

---

## 1️⃣ Joining with Username

Flow:

* Player enters room code
* Enters username
* Server validates uniqueness
* Server creates Player object
* Lobby updates in real-time

Use WebSockets to update lobby instantly.

---

## 2️⃣ Host Page (Two Tabs is Perfect)

YES — you’re thinking correctly.

Host should have:

### Tab 1: Game Control

* Player list (alive/dead)
* Roles (visible to host)
* Force phase change
* End game button

### Tab 2: Display Mode

This is brilliant.
This is what gets projected.

Should show:

* Current phase
* Who died
* Nominees
* Vote results (if non-anonymous)
* Timer
* Remaining player count

No role leaks.

---

## 3️⃣ Custom Roles System

This is the most important structural piece.

Design it as:

* Role creation interface
* Host can:

  * Add role
  * Set description
  * Define win condition
  * Choose team alignment
  * Choose if it has night ability

When game starts:

* Host selects which roles are in play
* Server auto-assigns randomly

This makes your game infinitely expandable.

---

## 4️⃣ Info Panel (Role Encyclopedia)

This should:

* Be accessible anytime
* Show:

  * Role name
  * Description
  * Win condition
  * Alignment

This panel must NEVER reveal who has what.

---

## 5️⃣ Voting System (Structured Properly)

This should have 3 distinct states:

### A. Nomination Phase

Host:

* Adds nominees manually
* Finalizes nominee list

Server locks nominee list.

---

### B. Voting Phase

Each alive player:

* Sees nominee list
* Can vote once
* Vote is stored server-side
* Vote cannot be changed (or optionally configurable)

If anonymous:

* Store vote normally
* Don’t display voter names

If non-anonymous:

* Store vote mapping
* Display:
  John → Sarah
  Mike → Sarah
  Emily → Jake

Host sees live vote counts.

---

### C. Result Phase

Server:

* Tallies votes
* Handles tie rules
* Eliminates player
* Triggers death screen

---

## 6️⃣ Role Actions from Player Devices

Night phase:

Each role with ability:

* Gets a custom UI
* Can select target
* Submit action

Server:

* Collects all actions
* Resolves them in defined order
* Applies outcomes

You must define:
Action resolution order system.

Example:

1. Protection
2. Redirection
3. Kill
4. Investigation

This avoids logic chaos.

---

## 7️⃣ Automatic Win Detection

After:

* Each elimination
* Each night resolution

Run win logic.

Example:
If mafia >= villagers → Mafia wins
If mafia == 0 → Villagers win
Check custom role win conditions too.

This must be centralized in the backend.

---

## 8️⃣ Day & Night Screens

Each client UI should be role-aware:

### During Day:

* Alive players see:

  * Voting panel
  * Discussion timer
* Dead players see:

  * Spectator screen

### During Night:

* Only roles with actions see action UI
* Others see:
  “Night in progress…”

---

## 9️⃣ Death Screens

When player dies:

* Their device switches automatically
* Shows:

  * “You have been eliminated”
  * Their role
  * Spectator info

They lose voting and actions.

---

## 🔟 Host Display Screen (Public Board)

This is one of the most professional features.

Display:

* Phase
* Alive list
* Dead list
* Vote counts
* Nominees
* Timer

Never show:

* Role assignments
* Night actions
* Hidden info

